Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Strip @Thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). Halve, peel, and finely chop @Shallot{1}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, half the chopped thyme, and a pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and crisp, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While veggies roast, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Transfer to a second baking sheet.

Roast chicken on middle rack until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} and let rest a few minutes, then thinly slice crosswise.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add shallot and remaining chopped thyme. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Fig Jam{1}, and 1⁄4 cup water (1⁄2 cup for 4 servings). Simmer until thick and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @Butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide potatoes, carrots, and chicken between plates. Drizzle pan sauce over chicken and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.